@startuml BABIFIX - Séquence Gestion des Litiges
!theme plain

skinparam backgroundColor #E3F2FD
skinparam sequenceStyle uml2

skinparam actor {
  BackgroundColor #90CAF9
  BorderColor #1976C2
}

skinparam entity {
  BackgroundColor #C8E6C9
  BorderColor #2E7D32
}

skinparam boundary {
  BackgroundColor #FFE082
  BorderColor #FF8F00
}

skinparam control {
  BackgroundColor #E1BEE7
  BorderColor #7B1FA2
}

skinparam arrow {
  Color #64B5F6
}

title **BABIFIX** - Séquence Litiges & Résolution\nDispute Management Flow

actor "Client" as Client
actor "Prestataire" as Prestataire
actor "Administrateur" as Admin
participant "BABIFIX Client\n(Flutter)" as AppClient
participant "BABIFIX Pro\n(Flutter)" as AppPro
participant "BABIFIX Admin\n(Web)" as AdminPanel
participant "Django API" as API
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant "Firebase\n(FCM)" as FCM
participant "Email\n(SMTP)" as Email

== Ouverture d'un litige ==

Client -> AppClient : Signale un problème
AppClient -> AppClient : Sélectionne motif\n(multiples choix)

alt Motifs disponibles
  note right of AppClient
    - Prestation non réalisée
    - Qualité insuffisante
    - Comportement inapproprié
    - Montant incorrect
    - Autre
  end note
end

AppClient -> AppClient : Ajoute description\n(max 1000 caractères)
AppClient -> AppClient : Upload preuves\n(photos, max 5)

AppClient -> API : POST /api/disputes/\n{booking_id, motif, description, photos}
activate API
API -> API : Validate booking ownership
API -> API : Check booking status\n(must be IN_PROGRESS/WAITING)
API -> DB : Create Dispute record\n(status: OPEN)
DB --> API : Dispute #D-2024-001
API -> DB : Update Reservation\n(dispute_ouverte: true)
API -> DB : Lock payment\n(cash_flow_status: frozen)
API --> AppClient : 201 Created\n{dispute_id, status}
deactivate API

API -> FCM : Send push to Admin\n(type: dispute, booking_id)
activate FCM
FCM -> AdminPanel : Notification badge\n(+1 litige en attente)
deactivate FCM

API -> Email : Send to Admin\n(subject: "Nouveau litige #D-2024-001")
activate Email
Email --> API : Email sent
deactivate Email

== Consultation par le prestataire ==

Prestataire -> AppPro : Voit notification litige
AppPro -> API : GET /api/disputes/{id}/
activate API
API -> DB : Fetch dispute details
API --> AppPro : Dispute details\n+ photos preuves client
deactivate API

AppPro -> AppPro : Consulte les détails
Prestataire -> AppPro : Ajoute sa réponse\n+ preuves contraires

AppPro -> API : PUT /api/disputes/{id}/\n{response, photos_defense}
activate API
API -> DB : Update Dispute\n(response, defense_photos)
API --> AppPro : Dispute updated
deactivate API

API -> FCM : Notify Client\n(type: dispute_response)
activate FCM
FCM -> AppClient : "Le prestataire\na répondu"
deactivate FCM

== Décision administrative ==

Admin -> AdminPanel : Ouvre liste litiges
AdminPanel -> API : GET /api/admin/disputes/\n?status=OPEN
activate API
API -> DB : Fetch open disputes\n(with related booking)
API --> AdminPanel : Liste litiges\n(priorité, ancienneté)
deactivate API

Admin -> AdminPanel : Sélectionne litige
AdminPanel -> API : GET /api/admin/disputes/{id}/
API --> AdminPanel : Détails complets\n(versions client + prestataire)

Admin -> AdminPanel : Analyse les preuves\n(photos côté client)\n(photos côté prestataire)

alt Option 1: Rembourser le client
  Admin -> AdminPanel : Clique "Rembourser client"
  AdminPanel -> AdminPanel : Confirme action
  AdminPanel -> API : PUT /api/admin/disputes/{id}/\n{decision: REFUND}
  activate API
  API -> DB : Update Dispute\n(decision: REFUND, resolved_at)
  API -> DB : Update Payment\n(state: REFUNDED, refund_client: true)
  API -> DB : Update Reservation\n(dispute_ouverte: false)
  API --> AdminPanel : Litige résolu
  deactivate API
  
  API -> FCM : Notify Client\n(type: refund_done)
  FCM -> AppClient : "Remboursement effectué"
  
else Option 2: Payer le prestataire
  Admin -> AdminPanel : Clique "Libérer paiement"
  AdminPanel -> API : PUT /api/admin/disputes/{id}/\n{decision: RELEASE}
  activate API
  API -> DB : Update Dispute\n(decision: RELEASE, resolved_at)
  API -> DB : Update Payment\n(state: COMPLETE, release_provider: true)
  API -> DB : Update Reservation\n(dispute_ouverte: false)
  deactivate API
  
  API -> FCM : Notify Prestataire\n(type: payment_released)
  FCM -> AppPro : "Paiement libéré"
  
else Option 3: Partage 50/50
  Admin -> AdminPanel : Clique "Partage 50/50"
  AdminPanel -> API : PUT /api/admin/disputes/{id}/\n{decision: SPLIT}
  activate API
  API -> DB : Update Dispute\n(decision: SPLIT, resolved_at)
  API -> DB : Calculate split amounts
  API -> DB : Update Payment\n(half to client, half to provider)
  API -> DB : Update Reservation\n(dispute_ouverte: false)
  deactivate API
  
  API -> FCM : Notify both\n(type: payment_split)
  FCM -> AppClient : "Remboursement partiel"
  FCM -> AppPro : "Paiement partiel"
  
end

== Logging & Audit ==

API -> DB : Create AdminAuditLog\n(action: LITIGE_RESOLVED,\n target: dispute_{id})
activate DB
DB --> API : Audit logged
deactivate DB

API -> Email : Send resolution to both\n(subject: "Litige résolu")
activate Email
Email --> API : Emails sent
deactivate Email

== Délai automatique ==

alt Litige non traité pendant 7 jours
  note right of Admin
    Système envoie
    rappel automatique
  end note
  
  API -> API : Scheduled task\n(every day at 9h)
  API -> DB : Find disputes\n(status: OPEN, age > 7 days)
  API -> FCM : Urgent notification\nto Admin
  API -> Email : Escalation email\nto support@babifix.ci
end

@enduml
